text: Ungut District ()() is a district (bakhsh) in Germi County, Ardabil Province, Iran. At the 2006 census, its population was 27,494, in 5,626 families. The District has one city: Tazeh Kand-e Angut. The District has three rural districts (dehestan): Angut-e Gharbi Rural District, Angut-e Sharqi Rural District, and Pain Barzand Rural District. == References == Category:Districts of Ardabil Province Category:Germi County
